  "market_context": "ETH on the daily chart shows a consolidation with highs swept first, then an aggressive expansion through the lows followed by an aggressive return back into the range, forming a higher-time-frame wick/reversal candle. Equal highs above the range serve as the draw on liquidity.",
  "key_observation": "The daily reversal candle was only candle 3 in the swing initially (no higher low on the right side), so the analyst waited one more day for a confirmed swing low (higher low on each side) before looking for hourly continuation entries toward equal highs.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Identify daily structure: consolidation with highs taken first, then aggressive sweep of the consolidation lows and aggressive return back inside — a higher-time-frame wick/reversal signature.",
    "Note the aggressive bullish daily closure but observe the low does not yet have a higher low on each side, meaning this is candle 3 in the swing, not a confirmed swing low.",
    "Wait one additional day until a higher low forms on the right side, confirming the daily swing low; keep equal highs above as the draw on liquidity.",
    "Anticipate price to support in the upper half (body-to-body) of candle 3 for a continuation higher.",
    "Drop to the 1-hour timeframe: observe expansion away from the low, expecting any retracement to hold and form lower-time-frame swing lows on side with the move.",
    "During London, price retraces into the upper-half area and produces a closure through the series of down-close candles into the level — a bullish change in state of delivery.",
    "Drop to 5-minute: wait for lows to be swept and then a closure through the down-close candles that formed that low to confirm a lower-time-frame bullish reversal.",
    "If first entry is missed, look for a continuation entry on a retracement into a fair value gap with a closure through the opposing candle into it.",
    "Enter with stop on the body low of the order block, targeting 2R toward the equal highs."
  ],
  "outcome": "The continuation entry off the fair value gap retracement expanded higher and hit the 2R target.",
  "lessons": "A daily reversal candle alone is not a swing low — it must have a higher low on each side. Waiting one extra day for the confirmed swing point, then drilling down to hourly/5-minute for a CISD or fair value gap continuation entry, yields a clean 2R setup toward HTF liquidity.",
